hands_on_practices.problem:
Let $A$ be a $2 \times 2$ matrix with real entries. The trace of $A$, denoted $\text{tr}(A)$, is 10 and the determinant of $A$, denoted $\det(A)$, is 25. Furthermore, it is known that $A$ is not a scalar multiple of the $2 \times 2$ identity matrix $I$.

Which of the following matrices must be the Jordan canonical form of $A$?

A. $
\begin{pmatrix}
10  0 \\
0  0
\end{pmatrix}
$

B. $
\begin{pmatrix}
5  0 \\
0  5
\end{pmatrix}
$

C. $
\begin{pmatrix}
5  1 \\
0  5
\end{pmatrix}
$

D. $
\begin{pmatrix}
25  0 \\
0  1
\end{pmatrix}
$

E. $
\begin{pmatrix}
10  1 \\
0  10
\end{pmatrix}
$
